<PageLayout title="About Us" description="Why mbpstobytes.com exists—an ultra-fast Mbps to Bytes/s converter built for clarity, speed, and privacy.">
  <section class="space-y-5 mt-4 text-slate-700">
    <p>
      mbpstobytes.com was built for one surprisingly common moment: you run a speed test, it says “100 Mbps,” and then your download manager reports something like “12.5 MB/s.” People assume something is broken—when it’s actually just
      <strong>bits vs bytes</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>So I made a tool that’s intentionally simple: type in Mbps (or Bytes/s), and the result updates instantly. No extra steps, no confusing toggles, no “wait for calculate.” Just clean conversions you can trust for quick comparisons.</p>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">What this tool does</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li><strong>Real-time conversion</strong> between Mbps and Bytes per second (B/s)</li>
      <li><strong>Helpful equivalents</strong> like KB/s and MB/s so you can match what apps display</li>
      <li><strong>Decimals control</strong> so the numbers look clean in reports and messages</li>
      <li><strong>Share/copy support</strong> to quickly send a summary to a client or teammate</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">What we care about</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc">
      <li><strong>Clarity over clutter.</strong> The interface stays minimal so the math stays obvious.</li>
      <li><strong>Speed.</strong> The calculator should feel instant—even on mid-range phones.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy by default.</strong> You shouldn’t need an account to do a simple conversion.</li>
      <li><strong>Practical accuracy.</strong> We use the common networking convention (1 Mbps = 1,000,000 bits/s) and clearly explain where real-world overhead can affect results.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-2xl">Say hello</h2>
    <p>
      Found an issue, want a feature (like binary unit options or more charts), or have feedback on the UX? Send a message via the <a href="/contact-us/" class="text-sky-800 hover:underline">contact page</a>. Real user feedback is what keeps this tool sharp.
    </p>

    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: December 6, 2025</p>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
